<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<rules>

  <rule>
    <description>
      <name>BYOVD - kernel driver loaded from user/temp-writable location</name>
      <category>Defense Evasion</category>
      <explanation>A kernel driver was loaded from a directory that is writable by non-privileged users or is a temporary location (user profile, ProgramData, Temp, Downloads, Desktop, PerfLogs, Public). Legitimate drivers load from System32\drivers, the DriverStore, or WinSxS. Loading a driver from a staging directory is the generic hallmark of Bring Your Own Vulnerable Driver (BYOVD), independent of the specific driver.</explanation>
      <os>Windows</os>
      <mitreattackid>T1068</mitreattackid>
      <mitreattackid>T1543.003</mitreattackid>
      <maliciousCauses>An attacker dropped a signed-but-vulnerable driver to a writable path and loaded it to gain kernel execution, typically to disable or blind the EDR (EDRKillShifter, EDRSandblast, Terminator/Spyboy, KDMapper, etc.).</maliciousCauses>
      <benignCauses>Rare. Some installers briefly stage drivers in Temp, but loading a running kernel driver from a user-writable path outside the normal driver stores is not expected.</benignCauses>
      <recommendedActions>Review [navigation:process_details] for the loading process and the driver file, check the signer/hash against the Microsoft vulnerable driver blocklist, and inspect [navigation:computer_details] for EDR telemetry gaps around this time. [remediation:kill]</recommendedActions>
      <guid>8bd849c3-9966-4a7f-acba-a29b5eeaff0c</guid>
    </description>
    <definition>
      <operations>
        <operation type="LoadDriver">
          <operator type="OR">
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Users\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Temp\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\AppData\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Downloads\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Desktop\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\ProgramData\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\PerfLogs\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Public\" />
          </operator>
        </operation>
      </operations>
    </definition>
    <maliciousTarget name="module" />
  </rule>

  <rule>
    <description>
      <name>BYOVD - kernel-mode service installed from user/temp-writable location</name>
      <category>Defense Evasion</category>
      <explanation>A kernel-mode service (Type = DriverType) was registered with the SCM whose image binary resides in a user- or temp-writable directory. BYOVD tooling drops a vulnerable driver and creates a kernel service on the fly to load it. Catches the registration even if the subsequent load is deferred or blocked.</explanation>
      <os>Windows</os>
      <mitreattackid>T1068</mitreattackid>
      <mitreattackid>T1543.003</mitreattackid>
      <maliciousCauses>Creation of a kernel service pointing at an attacker-dropped vulnerable driver, used to obtain kernel execution and tamper with security products.</maliciousCauses>
      <benignCauses>Some third-party software installs kernel services, but legitimate ones place the driver under System32\drivers or the DriverStore, not in Temp or a user profile.</benignCauses>
      <recommendedActions>Correlate with Security event 7045, verify the driver signer/hash, and check for EDR telemetry loss on [navigation:computer_details]. [remediation:kill]</recommendedActions>
      <guid>9a2572b5-4a65-40b3-b6ed-a1f81dade117</guid>
    </description>
    <definition>
      <operations>
        <operation type="ServiceInstalled">
          <operator type="AND">
            <condition component="Service" property="Type" condition="is" value="1" />
            <operator type="OR">
              <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Users\" />
              <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Temp\" />
              <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\AppData\" />
              <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Downloads\" />
              <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Desktop\" />
              <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\ProgramData\" />
              <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\PerfLogs\" />
              <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="contains" value="\Public\" />
            </operator>
          </operator>
        </operation>
      </operations>
    </definition>
    <maliciousTarget name="module" />
  </rule>

  <rule>
    <description>
      <name>BYOVD - kernel driver loaded outside standard driver directories (broad)</name>
      <category>Defense Evasion</category>
      <explanation>A kernel driver was loaded from a path outside System32 and outside the WinSxS/DriverStore locations. This is a broad net for BYOVD and unusual driver placement. Higher potential for false positives from legitimate third-party drivers that load from vendor folders under Program Files, so baseline your environment and exclude known-good vendor paths before raising severity.</explanation>
      <os>Windows</os>
      <mitreattackid>T1068</mitreattackid>
      <mitreattackid>T1543.003</mitreattackid>
      <maliciousCauses>A vulnerable or malicious driver loaded from a non-standard location as part of a BYOVD or rootkit-style attack.</maliciousCauses>
      <benignCauses>Legitimate third-party drivers occasionally load from vendor directories under Program Files. Establish a baseline and add exclusions before treating this as high severity.</benignCauses>
      <recommendedActions>Compare the driver against known-good vendor drivers, verify signer and hash, and review the loading process lineage in [navigation:process_details].</recommendedActions>
      <guid>756ad6a0-d5b3-43e0-a617-8f990bf9f054</guid>
    </description>
    <definition>
      <operations>
        <operation type="LoadDriver">
          <operator type="AND">
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="notstarts" value="%SYSTEM%" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="notcontains" value="\WinSxS\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="notcontains" value="\DriverStore\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="notcontains" value="\System32\" />
            <condition component="FileItem" property="Path" condition="notcontains" value="\SysWOW64\" />
          </operator>
        </operation>
      </operations>
    </definition>
    <maliciousTarget name="module" />
  </rule>

</rules>
